      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:2:73:13",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " شِرَاءِ الثَّمَرَةِ قَالَ إِذَا سَاوَتْ شَيْئاً فَلَا بَأْسَ بِشِرَائِهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding buying the fruit. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘When something is unspoilt, so there is no problem with buying it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "13. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hammad from al-Halabiy who has said the following: “About the case of buying fruits, abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘When it becomes something buying it is not harmful.’” "
        ]
      }
